{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}} The '''Valletta International Baroque Festival''' is one of the biggest music festivals of [[Malta]]. The programmatic focus is on [[baroque music]].
== History == Since its establishment in 2013, the ''Valletta International Baroque Festival'' is held every year in January and organized by the direction of [[Manoel Theatre]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20170828012231/http://www.visitmalta.com/de/event-details/2017-01/valletta-international-baroque-festival-9484 Valletta International Baroque Festival.] Information on the website Visitmalta.com. (English).</ref> The concerts and opera performances are presented in several Baroque buildings in the city of [[Valletta]].
Among the famous artists who have performed at the festival are [[Mahan Esfahani]], [[Philippe Herreweghe]], [[Christophe Rousset]] and [[Jordi Savall]].
On 26 January 2017 [[Reuben Pace]]'s [[Concertino (composition)|Concertino]] for guitar, [[harpsichord]] and orchestra was premiered at Manoel Theatre under the slogan ''Inspired by Baroque'' with the [[Malta Philharmonic Orchestra]] under the direction of [[Michelle Castelletti]] as well as the soloists [[Johanna Beisteiner]] (guitar) and [[Joanne Camilleri]] (harpsichord).<ref>[http://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20170122/arts-entertainment/a-baroque-world-premiere.637264 A baroque world premiere.] Article by Iggy Fenech, [[Times of Malta]], 22 January 2017. (English)</ref><ref>[http://operalounge.de/features/musikszene-festivals/malta-is-more Malta is more.] Article by Bernd Hoppe on the website of the magazine Opera Lounge, January 2017. (German)</ref> It was the first [[world premiere]] during the ''Valletta International Baroque Festival'' and signaled an artistic expansion of the festival's programme to contemporary works inspired by baroque music.
